Summary 

At 6.9%, the median gender pay gap is below the Office for National Statistics Annual Survey 

of Hours and Earnings 2017 figure for all employees and below the figure for the Education 

sector.  

The median gender pay gap figure of 6.9% when compared against the XpertHR 
benchmark figures, shows that the College’s mean gender pay gap is significantly below 

the whole sample figure.  It is below the figure for organisations in the same sector and 

significantly below the figure for organisations in the same industry. It is significantly below the 

figure for organisations with a similar financial turnover and significantly below organisations 

that have a similar number of employees. 

